00:19.560 --> 00:23.160
Recording by Simon Wainwright.

00:23.160 --> 00:29.260
The Book of Isaiah, King James Version, Chapter 10.

00:30.080 --> 00:33.900
Woe unto them that decree unrighteous decrees,

00:34.100 --> 00:39.000
and that right grievousness which they have prescribed,

00:39.340 --> 00:42.340
to turn aside the needy from judgment,

00:42.420 --> 00:46.580
and to take away the right from the poor of my people,

00:46.940 --> 00:52.360
that widows may be their prey, and that they may rob the fatherless.

00:52.360 --> 00:55.960
And what will ye do in the day of visitation,

00:56.220 --> 01:00.300
and in the desolation which shall come from far?

01:00.740 --> 01:02.840
To whom will ye flee for help?

01:03.200 --> 01:06.020
And where will ye leave your glory?

01:06.440 --> 01:10.040
Without me they shall bow down under the prisoners,

01:10.220 --> 01:13.820
and they shall fall under the slain.

01:14.120 --> 01:18.120
For all this his anger is not turned away,

01:18.760 --> 01:21.800
but his hand is stretched out still.

01:22.800 --> 01:25.980
O Assyrian, the rod of my anger,

01:26.460 --> 01:30.500
and the staff in their hand of mine indignation,

01:30.740 --> 01:34.620
I will send him against an hypocritical nation,

01:34.920 --> 01:39.700
and against the people of my wrath will I give him a charge,

01:39.980 --> 01:43.400
to take the spoil and to take the prey,

01:43.660 --> 01:47.720
and to tread them down like the mire of the streets.

01:47.720 --> 01:53.580
Howbeit he meaneth not so, neither doth his heart think so,

01:53.880 --> 02:00.320
but it is in his heart to destroy, and cut off nations, not a few.

02:00.900 --> 02:05.100
For he sayeth, Are not my princes altogether kings?

02:05.660 --> 02:09.980
Is not Calno as Kar-Kamish?

02:10.400 --> 02:13.200
Is not Hamath as Arpad?

02:13.200 --> 02:17.140
Is not Samaria as Damascus?

02:17.820 --> 02:21.180
As my hand hath found the kingdoms of the idols,

02:21.780 --> 02:28.120
and whose graven images do excel them of Jerusalem and of Samaria,

02:28.540 --> 02:33.100
shall I not, as I have done unto Samaria and her idols,

02:33.260 --> 02:36.320
so do to Jerusalem and her idols?

02:36.900 --> 02:39.420
Wherefore it shall come to pass,

02:39.420 --> 02:45.280
that when the Lord hath performed his whole work upon Mount Zion,

02:45.660 --> 02:50.640
and on Jerusalem, I will punish the fruit of the stout heart

02:50.640 --> 02:55.480
of the king of Assyria, and the glory of his high looks.

02:55.940 --> 03:00.240
For he sayeth, By the strength of my hand I have done it,

03:00.240 --> 03:02.300
and by my wisdom.

03:02.580 --> 03:06.820
For I am prudent, and I have removed the bonds of the people,

03:06.820 --> 03:10.900
and have robbed their treasures, and I have put down the inhabitants

03:10.900 --> 03:12.700
like a valiant man.

03:13.560 --> 03:19.320
And my hand hath found, as a nest of riches of the people,

03:19.620 --> 03:25.300
and as one gathereth eggs that are left, have I gathered all the earth.

03:25.820 --> 03:32.620
And there was none that moved the wing, or opened the mouth, or peeped.

03:32.620 --> 03:36.960
Shall the axe boast itself against him that heweth therewith,

03:37.480 --> 03:43.340
or shall the saw magnify itself against him that shaketh it,

03:43.920 --> 03:49.100
as if the rod should shake itself against them that lift it up,

03:49.360 --> 03:55.520
or as if the staff should lift up itself as if it were no wood?

03:55.940 --> 04:02.100
Therefore shall the Lord, the Lord of hosts, send among his fat ones leanness,

04:02.100 --> 04:08.020
and under his glory he shall kindle a burning, like the burning of a fire.

04:08.420 --> 04:15.420
And the light of Israel shall be for a fire, and his holy one for a flame.

04:15.620 --> 04:21.560
And it shall burn and devour his thorns and his briars in one day,

04:22.140 --> 04:27.280
and shall consume the glory of his forest, and of his fruitful field,

04:27.280 --> 04:35.020
both soul and body, and they shall be as when a standard bearer fainteth.

04:35.500 --> 04:41.880
And the rest of the trees of his forest shall be few, that a child may write them.

04:42.820 --> 04:48.600
And it shall come to pass in that day, that the remnant of Israel,

04:49.040 --> 04:55.800
and such as are escaped of the house of Jacob, shall no more again stay upon him

04:55.800 --> 05:02.800
that smote them, but shall stay upon the Lord, the holy one of Israel, in truth.

05:03.440 --> 05:09.700
The remnant shall return, even the remnant of Jacob, unto the mighty God.

05:10.740 --> 05:18.980
For thou, thy people Israel, be as the sand of the sea, yet a remnant of them shall return.

05:19.340 --> 05:25.060
The consumption decreed shall overflow with righteousness.

05:25.060 --> 05:34.100
For the Lord God of hosts shall make a consumption even determined in the midst of all the land.

05:34.760 --> 05:41.740
Therefore, thus saith the Lord God of hosts, O my people that dwellest in Zion,

05:42.200 --> 05:46.880
be not afraid of the Assyrian. He shall smite thee with a rod,

05:47.200 --> 05:51.840
and shall lift up his staff against thee after the manner of Egypt.

05:51.840 --> 06:01.400
For yet a very little while, and the indignation shall cease, and mine anger in their destruction.

06:02.320 --> 06:06.280
And the Lord of hosts shall stir up a scourge for him,

06:06.660 --> 06:10.440
according to the slaughter of Midian at the rock of Oreb.

06:11.040 --> 06:18.000
And his rod was upon the sea, so shall he lift it up after the manner of Egypt.

06:18.000 --> 06:25.360
And it shall come to pass in that day, that his burden shall be taken away from off thy shoulder,

06:25.620 --> 06:32.340
and his yoke from off thy neck, and the yoke shall be destroyed because of the anointing.

06:33.620 --> 06:40.060
He is come to Ayathe. He is passed to Megrun.

06:40.060 --> 06:48.000
At Micmash, he hath laid up his carriages. They are gone over the passage.

06:48.320 --> 06:53.040
They have taken up their lodging and gibba. Ramah is afraid.

06:53.660 --> 06:59.600
Kabiah of Saul is fled. Lift up thy voice, O daughter of Gollum.

06:59.820 --> 07:04.000
Cause it to be heard unto Laish, O poor Anathoth.

07:05.000 --> 07:12.320
Madmenna is removed. The inhabitants of Gibbim gather themselves to flee.

07:13.000 --> 07:19.700
As yet shall he remain at Nob that day. He shall shake his hand against the mount

07:19.700 --> 07:27.860
of the daughter of Zion, the hill of Jerusalem. Behold, the Lord, the Lord of hosts shall lop

07:27.860 --> 07:36.720
the bough with terror, and the high ones of stature shall be hewn down, and the hearty shall be

07:36.720 --> 07:44.680
humbled. And he shall cut down the thickets of the forest with iron, and Lebanon shall be a mighty one.

07:45.280 --> 07:54.560
Chapter 11. And there shall come forth a rod out of the stem of Jesse, and a branch shall grow out

07:54.560 --> 08:02.880
of his roots. And the spirit of the Lord shall rest upon him, the spirit of wisdom and understanding,

08:03.060 --> 08:10.660
the spirit of counsel and might, the spirit of knowledge and of the fear of the Lord,

08:11.120 --> 08:16.680
and shall make him of quick understanding in the fear of the Lord. And he shall not judge

08:16.680 --> 08:23.700
after the sight of his eyes, neither reprove after the hearing of his ears, but with righteousness

08:23.700 --> 08:30.980
shall he judge the poor and reprove with equity for the meek of the earth. And he shall smite the

08:30.980 --> 08:38.240
earth with the rod of his mouth, and with the breath of his lips shall he slay the wicked.

08:39.020 --> 08:46.080
And righteousness shall be the girdle of his loins, and faithfulness the girdle of his reins.

08:46.600 --> 08:53.060
The wolf also shall dwell with the lamb, and the leopard shall lie down with the kid and the calf

08:53.060 --> 09:02.840
and the lion and the fatling together, and a little child shall lead them. And the cow and the bear

09:02.840 --> 09:09.980
shall feed, their young ones shall lie down together, and the lion shall eat straw like the ox.

09:10.720 --> 09:23.040
And the suckling child shall play on the hole, and the asp and the weaned child shall put his hand on

09:53.040 --> 09:59.880
to recover the remnant of his people, which shall be left from Assyria and from Egypt

09:59.880 --> 10:07.820
and from Pathros and from Cush and from Elam and from Shinar and from Hamath

10:07.820 --> 10:14.760
and from the islands of the sea. And he shall set up an ensign for the nations,

10:15.200 --> 10:21.540
and shall assemble the outcasts of Israel, and gather together the dispersed of Judah

10:21.540 --> 10:28.520
from the four corners of the earth. The envy also of Ephraim shall depart,

10:29.000 --> 10:35.740
and the adversaries of Judah shall be cut off. Ephraim shall not envy Judah, and Judah

10:35.740 --> 10:43.500
shall not vex Ephraim. But they shall fly upon the shoulders of the Philistines toward the west.

10:43.840 --> 10:50.120
They shall spoil them of the east together. They shall lay their hands upon Edom and Moab

10:50.120 --> 10:55.980
and the children of Ammon shall obey them, and the Lord shall utterly destroy the tongue

10:55.980 --> 11:02.620
of the Egyptian sea. And with his mighty wind shall he shake his hand over the river,

11:02.940 --> 11:10.720
and shall smite it in the seven streams, and make men go over Dry Shad. And there shall be

11:10.720 --> 11:18.560
an highway for the remnant of his people, which shall be left from Assyria, like as it was to

11:18.560 --> 11:28.220
Israel in the day that he came up out of the land of Egypt. Chapter 12. And in that day thou

11:28.220 --> 11:36.960
shalt say, O Lord, I will praise thee. Though thou wast angry with me, thine anger is turned away,

11:37.340 --> 11:45.240
and thou comfortest me. Behold, God is my salvation. I will trust and not be afraid,

11:45.240 --> 11:54.280
for the Lord Jehovah is my strength and my song. He also is become my salvation. Therefore, with

11:54.280 --> 12:01.420
joy shall ye draw water out of the wells of salvation, and in that day shall ye praise the

12:01.420 --> 12:10.380
Lord. Call upon his name. Declare his doings among the people. Make mention that his name is exalted.

12:10.380 --> 12:19.320
Sing unto the Lord, for he hath done excellent things. This is known in all the earth. Cry out

12:19.320 --> 12:26.520
and shout thou, inhabitant of Zion, for great is the Holy One of Israel in the midst of thee.

12:26.520 --> 12:34.700
End of chapters 10 through 12. Recording by Simon Wainwright.

